{
  "texts": [
    "For example, in the Dyna framework (Sutton 1991), planning is conducted only at previously visited states, and the model is sampled to generate 100 one-step transitions for each action derivation iteration.",
    "In the case of AlphaGo Zero (Silver et al. 2017), planning efforts are focused on the current state, with 1600 traces of Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) (Coulom 2006) iterations conducted at a depth of 200.",
    "The planning method also needs to be specified in this stage.",
    "The AI and RL communities have primarily utilized discrete planning method, such as probability-limited search (Lai 2015), breadth-limited depth-limited search (François-Lavet et al. 2019), and MCTS (Silver et al. 2017).",
    "However, there is also the option to employ differential planning methods, exploiting the differentiability of the learned model for a gradient-based approach."
  ]
}